(228, 1, '2018-03-27 17:40:16', '2018-03-27 17:40:16', 'This wine is a masterly blend of the Greek variety Mavroudi of Thrace at eighty-five percent and Merlot at fifteen percent.\n\nThe grapes have matured perfectly and healthy. Their early morning harvest and their promotion to the winery within one hour makes wine making possible right after grape picking.\n\nIn the application of the classic red winemaking with long extraction, the following stages are followed: Harvesting grapes, stalking and mincing, without being pressed.\n\nThis leads to an exceptional quality wine. The temperature of the alcoholic fermentation is kept strictly at 26 C in automatic vatifiers of five tons and the fermentation takes place in oak barrels', 'Apocalypsis', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '206-autosave-v1', '', '', '2018-03-27 17:40:16', '2018-03-27 17:40:16', '', 206, 'http://luculos.com/?p=228', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
